Bronca, Diego Maradona called it. The emotion was his driving force throughout his career. Marcela Mora y Araujo, translator of his autobiography El Diego, described it as representing ‘anger, fury, hatred, resentment and bitter discontent’.

It would appear Luis Suarez, perhaps the player most like Maradona at this World Cup, is motivated by bronca, too.

Nothing else explains his mood swings, his brilliant destructiveness, the intensity of his creative blaze and sudden self-immolation.

