The return is that nothing he does can be wrong in their eyes. Uruguay’s part in this Faustian pact is that they will defend the indefensible, endorse the ludicrous and feed  paranoia, a perverse victim mentality, that is plainly unhealthy.

Oscar Tabarez is a hugely respected coach on the South American continent, who even Maradona refers to as el maestro, yet he, too, was moved to foolishness by his refusal to acknowledge that Suarez had done wrong.

Tabarez claimed the allegations were a conspiracy, conducted by people ‘hiding in trees’. That Suarez’s act was beamed live across the world escaped him. Diego Lugano, Uruguay’s captain, said Chiellini was a snitch and had shown the referee an old scar.

